# Project statuses

## List a project's statuses

Returns a list of statuses belonging to a specified project.

```shell
curl "https://screendoor.dobt.co/api/projects/2/statuses?v=0&api_key=d9763djh1274"

# Example Response
[
<%= partial 'resources/status.json' %>]
```

### HTTP Request

`GET /projects/:project_id/statuses`

## Create a status

Creates a status for the specified project.

```shell
curl "https://screendoor.dobt.co/api/projects/2/statuses?v=0&api_key=d9763djh1274" \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -X POST \
  -d '
{
  "name": "Open"
}
'

# Example Response
<%= partial 'resources/status.json' %>
```

### HTTP Request

`POST /projects/:project_id/statuses`

### Options

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| name | string | | |

## Retrieve a single status

Retrieves a status by name.

```shell
curl "https://screendoor.dobt.co/api/projects/2/statuses/Open?v=0&api_key=d9763djh1274"

# Example Response
<%= partial 'resources/status.json' %>
```

### HTTP Request

`GET /projects/:project_id/statuses/:name`

## Update a status

Updates the specified status.

```shell
curl "https://screendoor.dobt.co/api/projects/2/statuses/ThisIsAStatusName?v=0&api_key=d9763djh1274" \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -X PUT \
  -d '
{
  "name": "Open"
}
'

# Example Response
<%= partial 'resources/status.json' %>
```

### HTTP Request

`PUT /projects/:project_id/statuses/:name`

## Reorder statuses

Sets a new sort order for a project's statuses.

```shell
curl "https://screendoor.dobt.co/api/projects/2/statuses/reorder?v=0&api_key=d9763djh1274" \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -X POST \
  -d '
{
  "names": ["Open", "Archived"]
}
'

# Example Response
[
{
  "name": "Open",
  "responses_count": 10
},
{
  "name": "Archived",
  "responses_count": 0
}
]
```

### HTTP Request

`POST /projects/:project_id/statuses/reorder`

## Delete a status

Deletes a status by name. Will return a `400 Bad Request` if you try to delete the only status for a project.

```shell
curl "https://screendoor.dobt.co/api/projects/2/statuses/Open?v=0&api_key=d9763djh1274" \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -X DELETE

# Example Response
Status: 204 No Content
```

### HTTP Request

`DELETE /projects/:project_id/statuses/:name`

